data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but in EF Core 11 that opt-in is gone — all synchronous calls **always throw** at runtime. There is no workaround to restore the old behavior.

Every method in your `ProductRepository` is affected:

| Breaks | Fix |
|--------|-----|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First(...)` | `await FirstAsync(...)` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

Your repository needs to become async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the chain must also be updated to `await` these methods. Remove any sync-over-async opt-in configuration you had — it's no longer recognized.
